{
  "stem": "5275.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was kind of a-- well, I don't want to say funny, but in a way, it was funny, because a few days before the war started, my mother persuaded my father-- my parents were divorced, by the way, in 1936, or 1935.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father remarried in 1936.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I lived with my father and stepmother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my mother, in 1939, persuaded my father to place me in a suburb of Warsaw with friends of theirs, because she suspected that there would be war.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, the first bombs that fell were on that place [LAUGHS] where I was in the suburbs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they told me to take a taxi and go back to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I went back to Warsaw, and I spent the Polish war in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, during the Polish war-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] it was a very difficult time, because Warsaw was declared an open city by the Germans and was bombarded day and night with artillery and planes.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were very, very close calls during that time-- 25 days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was part of the time with my father, and part of the time with my mother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were very, very lucky, because there were many people killed around us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were lucky we survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that time, we lived on [NON-ENGLISH], Ninth Street, which was a upper, middle-class neighborhood, next to the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a bomb fell on a gas station which was between the American embassy and our home, nearly destroying the apartment building.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So at that time, my father decided that maybe the Germans were trying to bomb the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he sent me to my mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I spent the rest of the war days with my mother in her apartment.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
